Title: Complete factorization of equations of motion in Wess-Zumino theory
Authors: D. Bazeia, J. Menezes, M.M. Santos
Comments: Revtex, 3 pages. Written after hep-th/0103041, to appear in PLB
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B521 (2001) 418-420
\\
  We prove that the equations of motion describing domain walls in a
Wess-Zumino theory involving only one chiral matter multiplet can be factorized
into first order Bogomol'nyi equations, so that all the topological defects are
of the Bogomol'nyi-Prasad-Sommerfield type.
